    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a real estate purchase, is a temporary holding account managed by a neutral third party, like a lawyer or title company. This account holds the earnest money deposit and other funds until all the conditions of the sale are met. You need it because it ensures that both you and the seller fulfill your respective obligations before the final transfer of ownership and funds occurs at closing. It acts as a secure bridge, preventing either party from unfairly taking the other's money.",
